subject: Re: [junit] please help: example recompile error
msgSnippet: Find the directory that contains the class Money and add that to your CLASSPATH both when you compile and when you run. Good luck. So said  qiong zhou  on
messageBody:
Find the directory that contains the class Money and add that to your
CLASSPATH both when you compile and when you run.

Good luck.

So said qiong zhou on 2003-02-25 --------------------

>HI,
>I am new to Junit. I have install it and run it
>correctly. And, I can compile a simple test case which
>is something like VectorTest.
>
>I used the following command to compile:
>mylocaldir>javac -classpath junit.jar
>junit\samples\money\MoneyTest.java
>
>The problem is when I recompile the MoneyTest.java in
>the samples package, it didn't work.
>Error messages are: cannot resolve symbol
>symbol: class Money
>location class junit.samples.money.MoneyTest
>.....
>
>Thanks a lot in advance.
>zhou.
